 

                                DRUG BUSTERS
                                ------------
                               By Dave Krohne

    Evil life threatening drugs are lurking around every corner,  you are 
armed with a small but powerful lazer device.  Can you rid your community 
from these drugs before they destroy you?

                    WARNING: THIS GAME MAY BE ADDICTING!
                    ------------------------------------

    GAME PLAY:  Drug Busters is completely mouse controlled.  Click left 
mouse button to start game then select the 1,2,3 buttons for game 
difficulty.  Button one is the safest game to play with only 20 seconds 
each module.  You will have less chances to score, but also less danger 
of getting killed.
    Zap a cigarette for 5 points, drops of booze for 10 points, jump over
the rolling pills for 15 points and zap the heroin needles for 25 points.
The more successful you are, the harder the game will be.  The right
mouse button may be used to exit the game at any time.



    PROGRAM NOTES:  Drug busters was created using BLITZ BASIC available
from M.A.S.T.  Blitz Basic offers full control of sprites, blits, sound 
and animation files.  The final product is 100% assembly code, producing 
slick super fast programs like this one.


   AUTHORS:  Dave Krohne has a B.A. degree from the University of Redlands.
Steve Beam studied art at the California Institute of Fine Arts.  Together
they created the Barney Bear Adventure series for Free Spirit Software.  
Currently they are working educational software for Commodore's CDTV, 
also math & reading software for grades 1-3.


